<br>
From this point on, it's a spending game, you either need to camp drops or grind cash and spend alot.<br>
<br>
- Shoulders: Dwarven plate (500 to 1k +5 AC)<br>
- Hands: Cobalt (3k + 14 AC) or look for a good deal on Blood Runed ( 5 to 9k + 15 AC)<br>
- Waist: Sash of the Dragon Born ( 4 to 6k +2 AC +2 haste) <br>
- Fingers: Platinum to Velium ( 1k +2 AC)<br>
- Helmet: Helm of Radulken ( 10k +14 AC)<br>
- Bracers: Brellium ( 20k for two, + 25 AC)<br>
<br>
I know it's an expensive list, but it'll basically turn <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=487230">you</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> into <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=343063">me</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.  It's only fair to point out though that I spend a fortune on him regularly to buy the best I can afford.  I'm a big believer in saving up for &quot;big&quot; upgrades, going to gear you can wear until you get lucky on a real raid whenever possible.<br>
<br>
I'd put the pink helm (Helm of Radulken) and the Brellium bracers on that list, even though the three of them will probably cost you 30k when all said and done.  You'll be able to wear them a very long time. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub38.ezboard.com/feqtraderscornerfrm38.showMessage?topicID=409.topic"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.eq-viatores.org/sig.php"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nyssah@thesteelwarrior>Nyssah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/11/02 12:23:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4612.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: magelo</span><hr size=1> Absolutely upgrade to tattered mantle or crested spaulders, as has been previously suggested.  Additionally, if you have the money, buy SCHWs for haste, then you can upgrade the belt slot to an item with AC like spider fur belt.<br>
